From: tomasz-karczewski-red <tomasz.karczewski@redembedded.com>
Date: Tue, 27 Jan 2026 11:21:58 +0100

Currently following happens on reboot:

1/ system shutdown is started
2/ ocdm is stopped; awc eagerly tells wpeframework to
   restart the service
3/ AWCProxyContainer tries to start ocdm container & starts
   waiting for the container state change (AWCProxyContainer::waitForStateChange)
   note: the container start will be blocked in such case, but thunder is
   not notified about that
4/ wpeframework gets SIGTERM and starts shutting down before
   the state change happened

In such case, wpeframework shutdown is blocked on AWCProxyContainer::waitForStateChange
until timeout (6 seconds), delaying the shutdown (and risking getting SIGKILL'ed by systemd)

This patch introduces a mechanism for
AWCProxyContainer::waitForStateChange to
be notified about thunder exit, and break the waiting loop.


